July 10, 1939 Monday   Viola & I went to Sharkey Ona & girls staid with Jim. Lloyd come stay most of evening. Jim is worse

August 29, 1939 Tuesday  Margaret and Viola come back we work in apples this evening Ona Arlene Dennie & I all went to Sharky took chicken & stop at Virgie she is worse Viola & I stay at Ona a while to night Elmer went to Fred.
June 24, 1939 Saturday  Glen birthday 11 yrs. I made window curtains & clean around Jim feel worse to day Lloyd come after the Black cow. We send Black cow Calf and 2 shoats to Flemingsburg. Ina & Vick come thems Elmer & Viola all went to Ona to night awhile Milton birthday
August 7, 1939 Monday  Jim birthday 62 yrs I peel Apple Alene come made Kraut Louise here to Ona here this morning work out the last cabbage
May 18, 1939 Thursday  Viola here we Ironed Ona & Monnie & girls here we finish up Tulip quilt
May 14, 1939 Sunday  No one here. Elmer went to Sharkey & weeded on Tobacco bed I went to Ona so Jim did too.
August 16, 1939 Wednesday  Lloyd & Lill here. Effie & Thelma come Jim is poorly. Fred Edith Versa here to night Bertha Hiram here Roy Margie here all night.
January 21, 1939 Saturday (1/2)  Chester Barn raisin Arlene come after eggs Lloyd & Elmer went to Walter see about a horse Jim & I went to Chester John Hunt John Henry Johnson Jack Curtiss Reck & Omar Cooper Fred Hicks Cleve & Charley Johnson Clyde & Eugene Ratliff
July 11, 1939 Tuesday  (1/2)  Jim fell this morning at three o’clock he staid in bed all day couldn’t sit up Bill Florence Vina Arlie Lorena all here this morning picking berries. Viola & Martha went to Sharkey after Orange Ona come we wash & Ironed some this eve
January 8, 1939 Sunday  Julia & Irene Thornburg here this morning Walter went home after dinner. Ona & girls here Elmer went to Fred & George Caudill Heifer had a Bull calf. Jim & Elmer staid at barn & shop all night.
July 9, 1939 Sunday  Monnia Ona and girls here all eve Elmer never come home till one O’clock night Jim Jimerson, Clyde, Eugene all here.
July 26, 1939 Wednesday  (1/2)  Lloyd Lill Mary L. & Donald come but went home before 1 o’clock come in Edd Black car. I & Viola fix Apple for Apples Butter Maryle & Martha brought me a letter from Omar.
July 21, 1939 Friday  Ona wash Effie Glen went home Ona here Effie Filson caned beans for me Jim no better Effie F Ironed.
June 7, 1939 Wednesday   I wash & wash 1 quilt 1 Blanket Monnia is take flour home. Viola commence to work an embroidery.
February 7, 1939 Tuesday  Ina went to Post Office I quilted some wash out a few peices I went to Ona after Red Linnament
May 29, 1939 Sunday  (1/2)  Viola & I went to Mack it rain we stopped in at Susan Dorasa & June there Susan & John H had went to see J. E.  Johnson he crazy. We went on to Effie Vick & Ina was there we all went to Graveyard.
